tldr: The user requested to add a database and an admin dashboard to a sleep
  questionnaire application based on an SOW. The agent implemented a PostgreSQL
  database with Prisma, API routes for data storage and CSV export, and a simple
  password-protected admin dashboard, later simplifying the authentication using
  Next.js middleware.
overview: The user's intent was to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by
  adding robust data persistence and an administrative interface. The agent
  evaluated the existing codebase against the provided Statement of Work,
  identifying the need for a database to store questionnaire responses, API
  endpoints for data interaction, and a client-facing admin dashboard with
  authentication. Key decisions included using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma
  for the database, implementing a simple password-based authentication system,
  and creating a dashboard for viewing and exporting responses as CSV. The
  approach involved updating the questionnaire's demographic fields, defining a
  new Prisma model, building RESTful API routes, and developing the dashboard
  UI. A significant pivot occurred when the authentication system was simplified
  from a custom HMAC-signed session to a more streamlined Next.js
  middleware-based approach, improving code clarity and reducing complexity. The
  agent guided the user through database setup and performed browser testing to
  confirm the functionality, including questionnaire submission, admin login,
  and data retrieval.
